FT  22 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Chillington to sell Anglo-Eastern stake
Chillington Corporation, the conglomerate with interests in property,
plantations and engineering, is selling most of its holding in Anglo-Eastern
Plantations to Genton International of Hong Kong for Pounds 8.57m.
Following the deal Genton will make a full offer for the rest of
Anglo-Eastern at 68p a share, the price paid for the 12.6m shares (48.08 per
cent) from Chillington.
Chillington will be left with 291,232 shares, 257,800 warrants and unsecured
loan stock in Anglo-Eastern.
